# Prisma Production Safety

When Prisma schema changes are introduced, avoid `db push`-only workflows for production.

## Required Workflow

- Create a migration in `prisma/migrations/` for every schema change that impacts production.
- Prefer `prisma migrate dev` to generate migrations; use hand-written SQL only when needed.
- Before deployment, run `prisma migrate status` against the production `DATABASE_URL`.
- If production was hotfixed manually, add an idempotent migration (`IF NOT EXISTS` / guarded `DO $$ ... $$`) so migration history catches up safely.
- Deploy with `prisma migrate deploy` on production, never `prisma migrate dev`.

## Verification Checklist

- `prisma migrate status` reports expected pending/applied migrations.
- `prisma migrate deploy` succeeds on production.
- `prisma migrate diff --from-url <prod> --to-schema-datamodel prisma/schema.prisma --script` has no unexpected drift.
